        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(web-ui): skip hidden subagent picker pages",
        "body": "Fixes #89249.\n\nSummary:\n- Advance the chat session picker through raw `sessions.list` pages that add no visible rows after hidden spawn-child subagent filtering.\n- Stop showing raw total counts when the picker is filtering out loaded rows, avoiding misleading states like `1 / 177`.\n- Add browser E2E regression coverage for a hidden-only page followed by a visible session page.\n\nSurface area:\n- No public config schema/options changes.\n- No plugin API/contract changes.\n- No new CLI flags, env vars, migrations, or setup surface.\n\nValidation:\n- `OPENCLAW_CAPTURE_UI_PROOF=1 OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/e2e/chat-picker-pagination.e2e.test.ts --reporter=dot` -> 1 file, 2 passed; screenshot proof captured at `.artifacts/pr-89323-control-ui-proof/chat-picker-hidden-page-skip.png` (1280x900 PNG).\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts -t \"chat session picker\" --reporter=dot` -> 1 file, 6 passed, 89 skipped.\n- `node_modules/oxfmt/bin/oxfmt --check ui/src/ui/e2e/chat-picker-pagination.e2e.test.ts ui/src/ui/chat/session-controls.ts ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts` -> passed.\n- `node_modules/oxlint/bin/oxlint --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.json ui/src/ui/e2e/chat-picker-pagination.e2e.test.ts ui/src/ui/chat/session-controls.ts ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts` -> 0 warnings/errors.\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD && git diff --check` -> passed.\n\nReal behavior proof:\n- Added a Playwright/Chromium Control UI E2E test that drives the actual chat picker in a browser against the mocked Gateway Control UI server.\n- The test creates a visible first page plus a hidden subagent row, then clicks Load More. The mocked backend returns a hidden-only raw page at offset `2`; the picker automatically requests offset `4` and renders the next visible top-level chat.\n- Assertions cover the requested offsets (`2`, then `4`), the visible picker count (`2`), absence of hidden subagent options, and removal of the Load More button after all visible rows are loaded.\n- Proof environment: WSL Ubuntu 24.04, Playwright Chromium, local `.artifacts/pr-89323-control-ui-proof/chat-picker-hidden-page-skip.png` screenshot from the passing browser run.\n\nSigned head:\n- `c6b0342f48c4a67d475d40e35edd40110a95cbcc` (`gpgsig` present)\n",
